#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:26
msgid ""
"The Origin of an object is shown in the 3D View by a small orange circle."
" This is highlighted in the image to the right by the red arrow. The "
"origin tells Blender the relative position of that object in 3D space. "
"What you see in the 3D view (vertices, edges etc) is what makes up the "
"object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:31
msgid ""
"While the Origin is equivalent to the center of the object, it does not "
"have to be located in the center of the *Mesh*. This means that an object"
" can have its center located on one end of the mesh or even completely "
"outside the mesh. For example, the orange rectangle in the image has its "
"Origin located on the far left of the mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:37
msgid "Now let us examine: Rotation around the individual origins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:39
msgid ""
"The blue rectangle has its Origin located in the center of the mesh, "
"while the orange rectangle has its Origin located on the left hand side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:41
msgid ""
"When the Pivot Point is set to *Individual Origins*, the center of each "
"object (indicated by the red arrow) remains in place while the object "
"rotates around it in the path shown by the black arrow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:47
msgid "In Edit Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:49
msgid ""
"In Edit Mode, setting the Pivot Point to Individual Origins produces "
"different results when the selection mode is set to Vertex, Edge or Face."
" For example, Vertex mode produces results similar to setting the pivot "
"point to median and Edge mode often produces distorted results. Using "
"Individual Origins in Face mode produces the most predictable results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:59
msgid ""
"Rotation of individual faces with the pivot point indicated by the image "
"text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:64
msgid ""
"Rotation of grouped faces with the pivot point indicated by the image "
"text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:67
msgid ""
"As can be seen in the images above, faces that touch each other will "
"deform when rotated when the pivot point is set to Individual Origins. "
"Faces that do not touch will rotate around their Individual Origins "
"(their center)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:76
msgid "Scaling with non-touching faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:81
msgid "Scaling with touching faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:84
msgid ""
"Groups of faces and Fgons can be scaled without their outside perimeter "
"being deformed. However, the individual faces inside will not be scaled "
"uniformly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:91
msgid "Modeling with faces and individual origins as the pivot point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:94
msgid ""
"Once you are aware of its limitations and pitfalls, this tool can save a "
"lot of time and lead to unique shapes. This \"anemone\" was modeled from "
"a 12 sided cylinder in about 10 minutes by repeatedly using this "
"workflow: extrusions of individual faces, scaling with *median as a pivot"
" point*, and scaling and rotations of those faces with *Individual "
"Origins as pivot points*."
msgstr ""

